# Key Architecture Components:

## Frontend (React.js - Port 3000)
- Single Page Application with React Router
- Firebase Authentication
- Material-UI/Custom CSS styling
- API integration with both backends
- Real-time SQL editor with Monaco Editor

## Backend 1 (Flask - Port 5000)
- AI-powered SQL query generation
- Natural language processing
- Model management (Ollama/Akash integration)
- Query explanation and conversation handling
- Schema generation from natural language

## Backend 2 (Flask - Port 5002)  
- Database connectivity (MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, etc.)
- SQL query execution
- Synthetic data generation
- Database schema extraction
- OCR and document processing

# Communication Flow:
Frontend ←→ Backend 1 (SQL Generation)
Frontend ←→ Backend 2 (Database Operations)
Backend 1 ←→ Backend 2 (Schema Auto-fetch)

# Deployment Structure:
- Frontend: Vercel/Netlify
- Backend 1: Heroku/Railway/DigitalOcean
- Backend 2: Heroku/Railway/DigitalOcean

# Environment Variables:
- Frontend: REACT_APP_BACKEND_1_URL, REACT_APP_BACKEND_2_URL
- Backend 1: SECONDARY_SERVICE_URL, FRONTEND_URL
- Backend 2: BACKEND_1_URL, FRONTEND_URL